48 void linux_fork_return(void *tableAddr)
49 {
50 #if defined(a64)
51  asmv("movq %0, %%cr3" ::"r"(tableAddr)); /* Load process page table */
52  asmv("movq $0, %rax\n"); /* Return 0 */
53  asmv("movq %r8, %rsp\n"); /* Restore stack pointer */
54  asmv("movq %r8, %rbp\n"); /* Restore base pointer */
55  asmv("swapgs\n"); /* Swap GS back to the user GS */
56  asmv("sti\n"); /* Enable interrupts */
57  asmv("sysretq\n"); /* Return to rcx address in user mode */
58 #elif defined(a32)
59 #warning "linux_fork_return not implemented for i386"
60 #endif
61  __builtin_unreachable();
62 }

64 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/read.2.html */
65 static ssize_t linux_read(SysFrm *, int fd, void *buf, size_t count)
66 {
67  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
68  void *pBuf = pcb->PageTable->Get(buf);
69 
70  function("%d, %p, %d", fd, buf, count);
71  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
72  ssize_t ret = fdt->_read(fd, pBuf, count);
73  if (ret >= 0)
74  fdt->_lseek(fd, ret, SEEK_CUR);
75  return ret;
76 }

80 {
81  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;

83 
84  function("%d, %p, %d", fd, buf, count);
85  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
86  ssize_t ret = fdt->_write(fd, pBuf, count);
87  if (ret)
88  fdt->_lseek(fd, ret, SEEK_CUR);

92 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/open.2.html */
93 static int linux_open(SysFrm *sf, const char *pathname, int flags, mode_t mode)
94 {
95  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
96  const char *pPathname = pcb->PageTable->Get(pathname);
97 
98  function("%s, %d, %d", pPathname, flags, mode);
99 
100  if (flags & 0200000 /* O_DIRECTORY */)
101  {
102  vfs::Node *node = fs->GetNodeFromPath(pPathname);
103  if (!node)
104  {
105  debug("Couldn't find %s", pPathname);
106  return -ENOENT;
107  }
108 
109  if (node->Type != vfs::NodeType::DIRECTORY)
110  {
111  debug("%s is not a directory", pPathname);
112  return -ENOTDIR;
113  }
114  }
115 
116  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
117  return fdt->_open(pPathname, flags, mode);
118 }

202 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/mmap.2.html */
203 static void *linux_mmap(SysFrm *, void *addr, size_t length, int prot,
204  int flags, int fildes, off_t offset)
205 {
206  static_assert(PROT_NONE == sc_PROT_NONE);
207  static_assert(PROT_READ == sc_PROT_READ);
208  static_assert(PROT_WRITE == sc_PROT_WRITE);
209  static_assert(PROT_EXEC == sc_PROT_EXEC);
210 
211  int new_flags = 0;
212  if (flags & MAP_SHARED)
213  {
214  new_flags |= sc_MAP_SHARED;
215  flags &= ~MAP_SHARED;
216  }
217  if (flags & MAP_PRIVATE)
218  {
219  new_flags |= sc_MAP_PRIVATE;
220  flags &= ~MAP_PRIVATE;
221  }
222  if (flags & MAP_FIXED)
223  {
224  new_flags |= sc_MAP_FIXED;
225  flags &= ~MAP_FIXED;
226  }
227  if (flags & MAP_ANONYMOUS)
228  {
229  new_flags |= sc_MAP_ANONYMOUS;
230  flags &= ~MAP_ANONYMOUS;
231  }
232  if (flags)
233  fixme("unhandled flags: %#x", flags);
234  flags = new_flags;
235 
236  if (length == 0)
237  return (void *)-EINVAL;
238 
239  bool p_None = prot & sc_PROT_NONE;
240  bool p_Read = prot & sc_PROT_READ;
241  bool p_Write = prot & sc_PROT_WRITE;
242  bool p_Exec = prot & sc_PROT_EXEC;
243 
244  bool m_Shared = flags & sc_MAP_SHARED;
245  bool m_Private = flags & sc_MAP_PRIVATE;
246  bool m_Fixed = flags & sc_MAP_FIXED;
247  bool m_Anon = flags & sc_MAP_ANONYMOUS;
248 
249  UNUSED(p_None);
250  UNUSED(m_Anon);
251 
252  debug("None:%d Read:%d Write:%d Exec:%d",
253  p_None, p_Read, p_Write, p_Exec);
254 
255  debug("Shared:%d Private:%d Fixed:%d Anon:%d",
256  m_Shared, m_Private, m_Fixed, m_Anon);
257 
258  int UnknownFlags = flags & ~(sc_MAP_SHARED |
259  sc_MAP_PRIVATE |
260  sc_MAP_FIXED |
261  sc_MAP_ANONYMOUS);
262  if (UnknownFlags)
263  {
264  /* We still have some flags missing afaik... */
265  fixme("Unknown flags: %x", UnknownFlags);
266  /* Allow? */
267  }
268 
269  if (offset % PAGE_SIZE)
270  return (void *)-EINVAL;
271 
272  if (uintptr_t(addr) % PAGE_SIZE && m_Fixed)
273  return (void *)-EINVAL;
274 
275  if ((m_Shared && m_Private) ||
276  (!m_Shared && !m_Private))
277  return (void *)-EINVAL;
278 
279  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
280  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
281  if (fildes != -1 && !m_Anon)
282  {
283  fixme("File mapping not fully implemented");
284  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
285  vfs::FileDescriptorTable::Fildes &_fd = fdt->GetDescriptor(fildes);
286  if (_fd.Descriptor != fildes)
287  {
288  debug("Invalid file descriptor %d", fildes);
289  return (void *)-EBADF;
290  }
291 
292  if (p_Read)
293  {
294  Memory::Virtual vmm = Memory::Virtual(pcb->PageTable);
295  void *pBuf = vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(length));
296  debug("created buffer at %#lx-%#lx",
297  pBuf, (uintptr_t)pBuf + length);
298 
299  uintptr_t mFlags = Memory::US;
300  if (p_Write)
301  mFlags |= Memory::RW;
302 
303  if (m_Fixed)
304  {
305  if (m_Shared)
306  return (void *)-ENOSYS;
307 
308  if (vmm.CheckRegion(addr, Memory::G))
309  {
310  debug("Address range %#lx-%#lx has a global page",
311  addr, (uintptr_t)addr + length);
312  // return (void *)-EINVAL;
313  }
314 
315  vmm.Map(addr, pBuf, length, mFlags);
316  off_t oldOff = fdt->_lseek(fildes, 0, SEEK_CUR);
317  fdt->_lseek(fildes, offset, SEEK_SET);
318 
319  ssize_t ret = fdt->_read(fildes, pBuf, length);
320 
321  fdt->_lseek(fildes, oldOff, SEEK_SET);
322 
323  if (ret < 0)
324  {
325  debug("Failed to read file");
326  return (void *)-ret;
327  }
328  return addr;
329  }
330  else
331  vmm.Map(pBuf, pBuf, length, mFlags);
332 
333  off_t oldOff = fdt->_lseek(fildes, 0, SEEK_CUR);
334  fdt->_lseek(fildes, offset, SEEK_SET);
335 
336  ssize_t ret = fdt->_read(fildes, pBuf, length);
337 
338  fdt->_lseek(fildes, oldOff, SEEK_SET);
339 
340  if (ret < 0)
341  {
342  debug("Failed to read file");
343  return (void *)-ret;
344  }
345  return pBuf;
346  }
347 
348  debug("???");
349  return (void *)-ENOSYS;
350  }
351 
352  intptr_t ret = (intptr_t)vma->CreateCoWRegion(addr, length,
353  p_Read, p_Write, p_Exec,
354  m_Fixed, m_Shared);
355 
356  return (void *)ret;
357 }

360 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/mprotect.2.html */
361 static int linux_mprotect(SysFrm *, void *addr, size_t len, int prot)
362 {
363  if (len == 0)
364  return -EINVAL;
365 
366  if (uintptr_t(addr) % PAGE_SIZE)
367  return -EINVAL;
368 
369  // bool p_None = prot & sc_PROT_NONE;
370  bool p_Read = prot & sc_PROT_READ;
371  bool p_Write = prot & sc_PROT_WRITE;
372  // bool p_Exec = prot & sc_PROT_EXEC;
373 
374  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
375  Memory::Virtual vmm = Memory::Virtual(pcb->PageTable);
376 
377  for (uintptr_t i = uintptr_t(addr);
378  i < uintptr_t(addr) + len;
379  i += PAGE_SIZE)
380  {
381  if (likely(!vmm.Check((void *)i, Memory::G)))
382  {
383  Memory::PageTableEntry *pte = vmm.GetPTE(addr);
384  if (pte == nullptr)
385  {
386  debug("Page %#lx is not mapped inside %#lx",
387  (void *)i, pcb->PageTable);
388  fixme("Page %#lx is not mapped", (void *)i);
389  continue;
390  return -ENOMEM;
391  }
392 
393  if (!pte->Present ||
394  (!pte->UserSupervisor && p_Read) ||
395  (!pte->ReadWrite && p_Write))
396  {
397  debug("Page %p is not mapped with the correct permissions",
398  (void *)i);
399  return -EACCES;
400  }
401 
402  // pte->Present = !p_None;
403  pte->UserSupervisor = p_Read;
404  pte->ReadWrite = p_Write;
405  // pte->ExecuteDisable = p_Exec;
406 
407  debug("Changed permissions of page %#lx to %s %s %s %s",
408  (void *)i,
409  (prot & sc_PROT_NONE) ? "None" : "",
410  p_Read ? "Read" : "",
411  p_Write ? "Write" : "",
412  (prot & sc_PROT_EXEC) ? "Exec" : "");
413 
414 #if defined(a64)
415  CPU::x64::invlpg(addr);
416 #elif defined(a32)
417  CPU::x32::invlpg(addr);
418 #elif defined(aa64)
419  asmv("dsb sy");
420  asmv("tlbi vae1is, %0"
421  :
422  : "r"(addr)
423  : "memory");
424  asmv("dsb sy");
425  asmv("isb");
426 #endif
427  }
428  else
429  {
430  warn("%p is a global page", (void *)i);
431  return -ENOMEM;
432  }
433  }
434 
435  return 0;
436 }

438 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/munmap.2.html */
439 static int linux_munmap(SysFrm *, void *addr, size_t length)
440 {
441  if (uintptr_t(addr) % PAGE_SIZE)
442  return -EINVAL;
443 
444  if (length == 0)
445  return -EINVAL;
446 
447  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
448  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
449  Memory::Virtual vmm = Memory::Virtual(pcb->PageTable);
450 
451  for (uintptr_t i = uintptr_t(addr);
452  i < uintptr_t(addr) + length;
453  i += PAGE_SIZE)
454  {
455  if (likely(!vmm.Check((void *)i, Memory::G)))
456  vmm.Remap((void *)i, (void *)i, Memory::P | Memory::RW);
457  else
458  warn("%p is a global page", (void *)i);
459  }
460 
461  /* TODO: Check if the page is allocated
462  and not only mapped */
463  vma->FreePages((void *)addr, TO_PAGES(length) + 1);
464  return 0;
465 }

493 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/readv.2.html */
494 static ssize_t linux_readv(SysFrm *sf, int fildes, const struct iovec *iov, int iovcnt)
495 {
496  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
497  const struct iovec *pIov = pcb->PageTable->Get(iov);
498 
499  ssize_t Total = 0;
500  for (int i = 0; i < iovcnt; i++)
501  {
502  debug("%d: iov[%d]: %p %d", fildes, i, pIov[i].iov_base, pIov[i].iov_len);
503 
504  if (!pIov[i].iov_base)
505  {
506  debug("invalid iov_base");
507  return -EFAULT;
508  }
509 
510  if (pIov[i].iov_len == 0)
511  {
512  debug("invalid iov_len");
513  continue;
514  }
515 
516  ssize_t n = linux_read(sf, fildes, pIov[i].iov_base, pIov[i].iov_len);
517  if (n < 0)
518  return n;
519  debug("n: %d", n);
520 
521  Total += n;
522  if (n < (ssize_t)pIov[i].iov_len)
523  {
524  debug("break");
525  break;
526  }
527  }
528  debug("readv: %d", Total);
529  return Total;
530 }

604 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/nanosleep.2.html */
605 static int linux_nanosleep(SysFrm *,
606  const struct timespec *req,
607  struct timespec *rem)
608 {
609  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
610  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);
611 
612  if (!vmm.Check((void *)req, Memory::US))
613  {
614  debug("Invalid address %#lx", req);
615  return -EFAULT;
616  }
617 
618  if (rem && !vmm.Check((void *)rem, Memory::US))
619  {
620  debug("Invalid address %#lx", rem);
621  return -EFAULT;
622  }
623 
624  auto pReq = pcb->PageTable->Get(req);
625  auto pRem = rem ? pcb->PageTable->Get(rem) : 0;
626 
627  if (pReq->tv_nsec < 0 || pReq->tv_nsec > 999999999)
628  {
629  debug("Invalid tv_nsec %ld", pReq->tv_nsec);
630  return -EINVAL;
631  }
632 
633  if (pReq->tv_sec < 0)
634  {
635  debug("Invalid tv_sec %ld", pReq->tv_sec);
636  return -EINVAL;
637  }
638 
639  debug("tv_nsec=%ld tv_sec=%ld",
640  pReq->tv_nsec, pReq->tv_sec);
641 
642  uint64_t nanoTime = pReq->tv_nsec;
643  uint64_t secTime = pReq->tv_sec * 1000000000; /* Nano */
644 
645  uint64_t time = TimeManager->GetCounter();
646  uint64_t sleepTime = TimeManager->CalculateTarget(nanoTime + secTime, Time::Nanoseconds);
647 
648  debug("time=%ld secTime=%ld nanoTime=%ld sleepTime=%ld",
649  time, secTime, nanoTime, sleepTime);
650 
651  while (time < sleepTime)
652  {
653  pcb->GetContext()->Yield();
654  /* TODO: sleep should be interrupted by
655  the signal and return errno EINTR */
656  time = TimeManager->GetCounter();
657  }
658  debug("time= %ld", time);
659  debug("sleepTime=%ld", sleepTime);
660 
661  if (rem)
662  {
663  pRem->tv_sec = 0;
664  pRem->tv_nsec = 0;
665  }
666  return 0;
667 }

675 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/shutdown.2.html */
676 static int linux_shutdown(SysFrm *, int sockfd, int how)
677 {

682 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/fork.2.html */
683 static pid_t linux_fork(SysFrm *sf)
684 {
685  TCB *Thread = thisThread;
686  PCB *Parent = Thread->Parent;
687 
688  PCB *NewProcess =
689  TaskManager->CreateProcess(Parent, Parent->Name,
690  Parent->Security.ExecutionMode,
691  true);
692  if (unlikely(!NewProcess))
693  {
694  error("Failed to create process for fork");
695  return -EAGAIN;
696  }
697 
698  NewProcess->PageTable = Parent->PageTable->Fork();
699  NewProcess->vma->SetTable(NewProcess->PageTable);
700  NewProcess->vma->Fork(Parent->vma);
701  NewProcess->ProgramBreak->SetTable(NewProcess->PageTable);
702  NewProcess->FileDescriptors->Fork(Parent->FileDescriptors);
703 
704  TCB *NewThread =
705  TaskManager->CreateThread(NewProcess,
706  0,
707  nullptr,
708  nullptr,
709  std::vector<AuxiliaryVector>(),
710  Thread->Info.Architecture,
711  Thread->Info.Compatibility,
712  true);
713  if (!NewThread)
714  {
715  error("Failed to create thread for fork");
716  delete NewProcess;
717  return -EAGAIN;
718  }
719  NewThread->Rename(Thread->Name);
720 
721  TaskManager->UpdateFrame();
722 
723  NewThread->FPU = Thread->FPU;
724  NewThread->Stack->Fork(Thread->Stack);
725  NewThread->Info.Architecture = Thread->Info.Architecture;
726  NewThread->Info.Compatibility = Thread->Info.Compatibility;
727  NewThread->Security.IsCritical = Thread->Security.IsCritical;
728  NewThread->Registers = Thread->Registers;
729 #if defined(a64)
730  NewThread->Registers.rip = (uintptr_t)linux_fork_return;
731  /* For sysretq */
732  NewThread->Registers.rdi = (uintptr_t)NewProcess->PageTable;
733  NewThread->Registers.rcx = sf->ReturnAddress;
734  NewThread->Registers.r8 = sf->StackPointer;
735 #else
736 #warning "sys_fork not implemented for other platforms"
737 #endif
738 
739 #ifdef a86
740  NewThread->GSBase = NewThread->ShadowGSBase;
741  NewThread->ShadowGSBase = Thread->ShadowGSBase;
742  NewThread->FSBase = Thread->FSBase;
743 #endif
744 
745  debug("ret addr: %#lx, stack: %#lx ip: %#lx", sf->ReturnAddress,
746  sf->StackPointer, (uintptr_t)linux_fork_return);
747  debug("Forked thread \"%s\"(%d) to \"%s\"(%d)",
748  Thread->Name, Thread->ID,
749  NewThread->Name, NewThread->ID);
750  NewThread->SetState(Tasking::Ready);
751 
752  // Parent->GetContext()->Yield();
753  return (int)NewProcess->ID;
754 }

756 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/execve.2.html */
757 static int linux_execve(SysFrm *sf, const char *pathname,
758  char *const argv[],
759  char *const envp[])
760 {
761  /* FIXME: exec doesn't follow the UNIX standard
762  The pid, open files, etc. should be preserved */
763  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
764  Memory::Virtual vmm = Memory::Virtual(pcb->PageTable);
765 
766  if (pathname == nullptr ||
767  !vmm.Check((void *)pathname, Memory::US) ||
768  !vmm.Check((void *)argv, Memory::US) ||
769  !vmm.Check((void *)envp, Memory::US))
770  return -ENOENT;
771 
772  const char *safe_path;
773  char **safe_argv;
774  char **safe_envp;
775  safe_path = (const char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(1);
776  safe_argv = (char **)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(MAX_ARG));
777  safe_envp = (char **)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(MAX_ARG));
778  {
779  Memory::SwapPT swap(pcb->PageTable);
780  size_t len = strlen(pathname);
781  memset((void *)safe_path, 0, PAGE_SIZE);
782  memcpy((void *)safe_path, pathname, len);
783 
784  const char *arg;
785  char *n_arg;
786  for (int i = 0; argv[i] != nullptr; i++)
787  {
788  arg = argv[i];
789  size_t len = strlen(arg);
790 
791  n_arg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(len));
792  memcpy((void *)n_arg, arg, len);
793  n_arg[len] = '\0';
794 
795  safe_argv[i] = n_arg;
796 
797  if (likely(i < MAX_ARG - 1))
798  safe_argv[i + 1] = nullptr;
799  }
800 
801  for (int i = 0; envp[i] != nullptr; i++)
802  {
803  arg = envp[i];
804  size_t len = strlen(arg);
805 
806  n_arg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(len));
807  memcpy((void *)n_arg, arg, len);
808  n_arg[len] = '\0';
809 
810  safe_envp[i] = n_arg;
811 
812  if (likely(i < MAX_ARG - 1))
813  safe_envp[i + 1] = nullptr;
814  }
815  }
816 
817  function("%s %#lx %#lx", safe_path, safe_argv, safe_envp);
818 
819 #ifdef DEBUG
820  for (int i = 0; safe_argv[i] != nullptr; i++)
821  debug("safe_argv[%d]: %s", i, safe_argv[i]);
822 
823  for (int i = 0; safe_envp[i] != nullptr; i++)
824  debug("safe_envp[%d]: %s", i, safe_envp[i]);
825 #endif
826 
827  vfs::RefNode *File = fs->Open(safe_path,
828  pcb->CurrentWorkingDirectory);
829 
830  if (!File)
831  {
832  error("File not found");
833  return -ENOENT;
834  }
835 
836  char shebang_magic[2];
837  File->read((uint8_t *)shebang_magic, 2);
838 
839  if (shebang_magic[0] == '#' && shebang_magic[1] == '!')
840  {
841  char *orig_path = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(strlen(pathname) + 1));
842  memcpy(orig_path, pathname, strlen(pathname) + 1);
843 
844  char *shebang = (char *)safe_path;
845  size_t shebang_len = 0;
846  constexpr int shebang_len_max = 255;
847  File->seek(2, SEEK_SET);
848  off_t shebang_off = 2;
849  while (true)
850  {
851  char c;
852  if (File->node->read((uint8_t *)&c, 1, shebang_off) == 0)
853  break;
854  if (c == '\n' || shebang_len == shebang_len_max)
855  break;
856  shebang[shebang_len++] = c;
857  shebang_off++;
858  }
859  shebang[shebang_len] = '\0';
860  debug("Shebang: %s", shebang);
861 
862  char **c_safe_argv = (char **)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(MAX_ARG));
863  int i = 0;
864  for (; safe_argv[i] != nullptr; i++)
865  {
866  size_t arg_len = strlen(safe_argv[i]);
867  char *c_arg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(arg_len));
868  memcpy((void *)c_arg, safe_argv[i], arg_len);
869  c_arg[arg_len] = '\0';
870 
871  c_safe_argv[i] = c_arg;
872  debug("c_safe_argv[%d]: %s", i, c_safe_argv[i]);
873  }
874  c_safe_argv[i] = nullptr;
875 
876  char *token = strtok(shebang, " ");
877  i = 0;
878  while (token != nullptr)
879  {
880  size_t len = strlen(token);
881  char *t_arg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(len));
882  memcpy((void *)t_arg, token, len);
883  t_arg[len] = '\0';
884 
885  safe_argv[i++] = t_arg;
886  token = strtok(nullptr, " ");
887  }
888 
889  safe_argv[i++] = orig_path;
890  for (int j = 1; c_safe_argv[j] != nullptr; j++)
891  {
892  safe_argv[i++] = c_safe_argv[j];
893  debug("clone: safe_argv[%d]: %s",
894  i, safe_argv[i - 1]);
895  }
896  safe_argv[i] = nullptr;
897 
898  delete File;
899  return linux_execve(sf, safe_argv[0],
900  (char *const *)safe_argv,
901  (char *const *)safe_envp);
902  }
903 
904  int ret = Execute::Spawn((char *)safe_path,
905  (const char **)safe_argv,
906  (const char **)safe_envp,
907  pcb, true,
908  pcb->Info.Compatibility);
909 
910  if (ret < 0)
911  {
912  error("Failed to spawn");
913  delete File;
914  return ret;
915  }
916 
917  delete File;
918  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
919  // ctx->Sleep(1000);
920  // pcb->SetState(Tasking::Zombie);
921  // pcb->SetExitCode(0); /* FIXME: get process exit code */
922  while (true)
923  ctx->Yield();
924  __builtin_unreachable();
925 }

931 
932  trace("Userspace thread %s(%d) exited with code %d (%#x)",

934  t->ID, status,
935  status < 0 ? -status : status);
936 
937  t->SetState(Tasking::Zombie);

941  __builtin_unreachable();

944 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/wait4.2.html */
945 static pid_t linux_wait4(SysFrm *, pid_t pid, int *wstatus,
946  int options, struct rusage *rusage)
947 {
948  static_assert(sizeof(struct rusage) < PAGE_SIZE);
949  /* FIXME: this function is very poorly implemented, the way
950  it handles the zombie & coredump processes is very
951  inefficient and should be rewritten */
952 
953  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
954  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);
955 
956  if (!vmm.Check(rusage, Memory::US) && rusage != nullptr)
957  {
958  debug("Invalid address %#lx", rusage);
959  return -EFAULT;
960  }
961 
962  if (pid == -1)
963  {
964  if (pcb->Children.empty())
965  {
966  debug("No children");
967  return -ECHILD;
968  }
969 
970  std::vector<PCB *> wChilds;
971  for (auto child : pcb->Children)
972  {
973  if (child->State == Tasking::Zombie)
974  {
975  if (wstatus != nullptr)
976  {
977  int *pWstatus = pcb->PageTable->Get(wstatus);
978  *pWstatus = 0;
979 
980  bool ProcessExited = true;
981  int ExitStatus = child->ExitCode.load();
982 
983  debug("Process returned %d", ExitStatus);
984 
985  if (ProcessExited)
986  *pWstatus |= ExitStatus << 8;
987  }
988 
989  if (rusage != nullptr)
990  {
991  size_t kTime = child->Info.KernelTime;
992  size_t uTime = child->Info.UserTime;
993  size_t _maxrss = child->GetSize();
994 
995  struct rusage *pRusage = pcb->PageTable->Get(rusage);
996 
997  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
998  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
999 
1000  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1001  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1002 
1003  pRusage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
1004  }
1005 
1006  child->SetState(Tasking::Terminated);
1007  return child->ID;
1008  }
1009 
1010  if (child->State == Tasking::CoreDump)
1011  {
1012  if (wstatus != nullptr)
1013  {
1014  int *pWstatus = pcb->PageTable->Get(wstatus);
1015  *pWstatus = 0;
1016 
1017  bool ProcessExited = true;
1018  int ExitStatus = child->ExitCode.load();
1019  bool ProcessSignaled = true;
1020  bool CoreDumped = true;
1021  int TermSignal = child->Signals->GetLastSignal();
1022 
1023  debug("Process returned %d", ExitStatus);
1024 
1025  if (ProcessExited)
1026  *pWstatus |= ExitStatus << 8;
1027 
1028  if (ProcessSignaled)
1029  *pWstatus |= TermSignal;
1030 
1031  if (CoreDumped)
1032  *pWstatus |= 0x80;
1033  }
1034 
1035  if (rusage != nullptr)
1036  {
1037  size_t kTime = child->Info.KernelTime;
1038  size_t uTime = child->Info.UserTime;
1039  size_t _maxrss = child->GetSize();
1040 
1041  struct rusage *pRusage = pcb->PageTable->Get(rusage);
1042 
1043  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1044  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1045 
1046  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1047  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1048 
1049  pRusage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
1050  }
1051 
1052  child->SetState(Tasking::Terminated);
1053  return child->ID;
1054  }
1055 
1056  if (child->State != Tasking::Terminated)
1057  wChilds.push_back(child);
1058  }
1059 
1060  if (wChilds.empty())
1061  {
1062  debug("No children");
1063  return -ECHILD;
1064  }
1065 
1066  fixme("Waiting for %d children", wChilds.size());
1067  pid = wChilds.front()->ID;
1068  }
1069 
1070  if (pid == 0)
1071  {
1072  fixme("Waiting for any child process whose process group ID is equal to that of the calling process");
1073  return -ENOSYS;
1074  }
1075 
1076  if (pid < -1)
1077  {
1078  fixme("Waiting for any child process whose process group ID is equal to the absolute value of pid");
1079  return -ENOSYS;
1080  }
1081 
1082  /* Wait for a child process, or any process? */
1083  PCB *tPcb = pcb->GetContext()->GetProcessByID(pid);
1084  if (!tPcb)
1085  {
1086  warn("Invalid PID %d", pid);
1087  return -ECHILD;
1088  }
1089 
1090  if (options)
1091  {
1092 #define WCONTINUED 1
1093 #define WNOHANG 2
1094 #define WUNTRACED 4
1095 #define WEXITED 8
1096 #define WNOWAIT 16
1097 #define WSTOPPED 32
1098  fixme("options=%#x", options);
1099  }
1100 
1101 #ifdef DEBUG
1102  foreach (auto child in pcb->Children)
1103  debug("Child: %s(%d)", child->Name, child->ID);
1104 #endif
1105 
1106  debug("Waiting for %d(%#lx) state %d", pid, tPcb, tPcb->State);
1107  while (tPcb->State != Tasking::Zombie &&
1108  tPcb->State != Tasking::CoreDump &&
1109  tPcb->State != Tasking::Terminated)
1110  pcb->GetContext()->Yield();
1111  debug("Waited for %d(%#lx) state %d", pid, tPcb, tPcb->State);
1112 
1113  if (wstatus != nullptr)
1114  {
1115  int *pWstatus = pcb->PageTable->Get(wstatus);
1116  *pWstatus = 0;
1117 
1118  bool ProcessExited = true;
1119  int ExitStatus = tPcb->ExitCode.load();
1120  bool ProcessSignaled = false;
1121  bool CoreDumped = false;
1122  bool ProcessStopped = false;
1123  bool ProcessContinued = false;
1124  int TermSignal = 0;
1125 
1126  debug("Process returned %d", ExitStatus);
1127 
1128  if (ProcessExited)
1129  *pWstatus |= ExitStatus << 8;
1130 
1131  if (ProcessSignaled)
1132  *pWstatus |= TermSignal;
1133 
1134  if (CoreDumped)
1135  *pWstatus |= 0x80;
1136 
1137  /* FIXME: Untested */
1138 
1139  if (ProcessStopped)
1140  *pWstatus |= 0x7F;
1141 
1142  if (ProcessContinued)
1143  *pWstatus = 0xFFFF;
1144 
1145  debug("wstatus=%#x", *pWstatus);
1146  }
1147 
1148  if (rusage != nullptr)
1149  {
1150  size_t kTime = tPcb->Info.KernelTime;
1151  size_t uTime = tPcb->Info.UserTime;
1152  size_t _maxrss = tPcb->GetSize();
1153 
1154  struct rusage *pRusage = pcb->PageTable->Get(rusage);
1155 
1156  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1157  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1158 
1159  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1160  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1161 
1162  pRusage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
1163  /* TODO: The rest of the fields */
1164  }
1165 
1166  return pid;
1167 }

1202 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/uname.2.html */

1267  if (uVer && strcmp(uVer, "auto") != 0)
1268  strncpy(uname.version, uVer, sizeof(uname.version));
1269  if (uMac && strcmp(uMac, "auto") != 0)
1270  strncpy(uname.machine, uMac, sizeof(uname.machine));
1271  ini_destroy(ini);
1272  }
1273  else
1274  warn("Couldn't open /etc/cross/linux");

1276  memcpy(pBuf, &uname, sizeof(struct utsname));

1278 }

1280 static int linux_fcntl(SysFrm *, int fd, int cmd, void *arg)
1281 {

1284  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);

1291  return fdt->GetFlags(fd);
1292  case F_SETFD:
1293  return fdt->SetFlags(fd, s_cst(int, (uintptr_t)arg));
1294  case F_GETFL:
1295  case F_SETFL:
1296  case F_SETOWN:
1297  case F_GETOWN:
1298  case F_SETSIG:
1299  case F_GETSIG:
1300  case F_GETLK:
1301  case F_SETLK:
1302  case F_SETLKW:
1303  case F_SETOWN_EX:
1304  case F_GETOWN_EX:
1305  {
1306  fixme("cmd %d not implemented", cmd);
1307  return -ENOSYS;
1308  }
1309  default:
1310  {
1311  debug("Invalid cmd %#x", cmd);
1312  return -EINVAL;
1313  }
1314  }
1315 }

1338 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/readlink.2.html */
1339 static ssize_t linux_readlink(SysFrm *, const char *pathname,
1340  char *buf, size_t bufsiz)
1341 {
1342  if (!pathname || !buf)
1343  return -EINVAL;
1344 
1345  if (bufsiz > PAGE_SIZE)
1346  {
1347  warn("bufsiz is too large: %ld", bufsiz);
1348  return -EINVAL;
1349  }
1350 
1351  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1352  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);
1353  if (!vmm.Check((void *)buf, Memory::US))
1354  {
1355  warn("Invalid address %#lx", buf);
1356  return -EFAULT;
1357  }
1358 
1359  const char *pPath = pcb->PageTable->Get(pathname);
1360  char *pBuf = pcb->PageTable->Get(buf);
1361  function("%s %#lx %ld", pPath, buf, bufsiz);
1362  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
1363  int fd = fdt->_open(pPath, O_RDONLY, 0);
1364  if (fd < 0)
1365  return -ENOENT;
1366 
1367  vfs::FileDescriptorTable::Fildes fildes = fdt->GetDescriptor(fd);
1368  vfs::Node *node = fildes.Handle->node;
1369  fdt->_close(fd);
1370 
1371  if (node->Type != vfs::NodeType::SYMLINK)
1372  return -EINVAL;
1373 
1374  if (!node->Symlink)
1375  {
1376  warn("Symlink null for \"%s\"?", pPath);
1377  return -EINVAL;
1378  }
1379 
1380  size_t len = strlen(node->Symlink);
1381  if (len > bufsiz)
1382  len = bufsiz;
1383 
1384  strncpy(pBuf, node->Symlink, len);
1385  return len;
1386 }

1488 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/reboot.2.html */
1489 static int linux_reboot(SysFrm *, int magic, int magic2, int cmd, void *arg)
1490 {
1491  if (magic != LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC1 ||
1492  (magic2 != LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2 &&
1493  magic2 != LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2A &&

1495  magic2 != LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2C))

1498  return -EINVAL;
1499  }
1500

1502

1505  {

1519

1524  {
1525  KPrint("Power down.");
1526 
1527  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
1528  ctx->CreateThread(ctx->GetKernelProcess(),
1529  Tasking::IP(KST_Shutdown))
1530  ->Rename("Shutdown");
1531  return 0;
1532  }
1533  case LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_RESTART2:
1534  {
1535  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);
1536  if (!vmm.Check(arg, Memory::US))
1537  {
1538  debug("Invalid address %#lx", arg);
1539  return -EFAULT;
1540  }
1541

1543  KPrint("Restarting system with command '%s'",
1544  (const char *)pArg);
1545 
1546  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
1547  ctx->CreateThread(ctx->GetKernelProcess(),
1548  Tasking::IP(KST_Reboot))
1549  ->Rename("Restart");
1550  break;

1553  case LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_CAD_OFF:
1554  case LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_SW_SUSPEND:
1555  case LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_KEXEC:
1556  {
1557  fixme("cmd %#x not implemented", cmd);
1558  return -ENOSYS;
1559  }

1563  return -EINVAL;

1565  }

1569 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/sigaction.2.html */
1570 static int linux_sigaction(SysFrm *, int signum,
1571  const struct sigaction *act,
1572  struct sigaction *oldact)
1573 {
1574  if (signum == linux_SIGKILL || signum == linux_SIGSTOP)
1575  {
1576  debug("Invalid signal %d", signum);
1577  return -EINVAL;
1578  }
1579 
1580  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1581  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);
1582 
1583  if (oldact && !vmm.Check(oldact, Memory::US))
1584  {
1585  debug("Invalid address %#lx", oldact);
1586  return -EFAULT;
1587  }
1588 
1589  if (act && !vmm.Check((void *)act, Memory::US))
1590  {
1591  debug("Invalid address %#lx", act);
1592  return -EFAULT;
1593  }
1594 
1595  debug("signum=%d act=%#lx oldact=%#lx", signum, act, oldact);
1596 
1597  auto pOldact = pcb->PageTable->Get(oldact);
1598  auto pAct = pcb->PageTable->Get(act);
1599  int ret = 0;
1600 
1601  if (pOldact)
1602  ret = pcb->Signals->GetAction(signum, pOldact);
1603 
1604  if (unlikely(ret < 0))
1605  return ret;
1606 
1607  if (pAct)
1608  ret = pcb->Signals->SetAction(signum, *pAct);
1609 
1610  return ret;
1611 }

1613 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/sigprocmask.2.html */
1614 static int linux_sigprocmask(SysFrm *, int how, const sigset_t *set,
1615  sigset_t *oldset, size_t sigsetsize)
1616 {
1617  static_assert(sizeof(sigset_t) < PAGE_SIZE);
1618 
1619  if (sigsetsize != sizeof(sigset_t))
1620  {
1621  warn("Unsupported sigsetsize %d!", sigsetsize);
1622  return -EINVAL;
1623  }
1624 
1625  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1626  const sigset_t *pSet = (const sigset_t *)pcb->PageTable->Get((void *)set);
1627  sigset_t *pOldset = (sigset_t *)pcb->PageTable->Get(oldset);
1628 
1629  debug("how=%#x set=%#lx oldset=%#lx",
1630  how, pSet ? *pSet : 0, pOldset ? *pOldset : 0);
1631 
1632  if (pOldset)
1633  *pOldset = pcb->Signals->GetMask();
1634 
1635  if (!pSet)
1636  return 0;
1637 
1638  switch (how)
1639  {
1640  case SIG_BLOCK:
1641  pcb->Signals->Block(*pSet);
1642  break;
1643  case SIG_UNBLOCK:
1644  pcb->Signals->Unblock(*pSet);
1645  break;
1646  case SIG_SETMASK:
1647  pcb->Signals->SetMask(*pSet);
1648  break;
1649  default:
1650  warn("Invalid how %#x", how);
1651  return -EINVAL;
1652  }
1653  return 0;
1654 }

1912 /* https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/getrandom.2.html */
1913 static ssize_t linux_getrandom(SysFrm *, void *buf,
1914  size_t buflen, unsigned int flags)
1915 {
1916  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1917  Memory::Virtual vmm(pcb->PageTable);
1918 
1919  if (!vmm.Check(buf, Memory::US))
1920  {
1921  debug("Invalid address %#lx", buf);
1922  return -EFAULT;
1923  }
1924 
1925  if (flags & GRND_NONBLOCK)
1926  fixme("GRND_NONBLOCK not implemented");
1927 
1928  if (flags & ~(GRND_NONBLOCK |
1929  GRND_RANDOM |
1930  GRND_INSECURE))
1931  {
1932  warn("Invalid flags %#x", flags);
1933  return -EINVAL;
1934  }
1935 
1936  if (flags & GRND_RANDOM)
1937  {
1938  uint16_t random;
1939  for (size_t i = 0; i < buflen; i++)
1940  {
1941  random = Random::rand16();
1942  {
1943  Memory::SwapPT swap(pcb->PageTable);
1944  ((uint8_t *)buf)[i] = uint8_t(random & 0xFF);
1945  }
1946  }
1947  return buflen;
1948  }
1949 
1950  return 0;
1951 }

2853 uintptr_t HandleLinuxSyscalls(SyscallsFrame *Frame)
2854 {
2855 #if defined(a64)
2856  if (Frame->rax > sizeof(LinuxSyscallsTableAMD64) / sizeof(SyscallData))
2857  {
2858  fixme("Syscall %d not implemented",
2859  Frame->rax);
2860  return -ENOSYS;
2861  }
2862 
2863  SyscallData Syscall = LinuxSyscallsTableAMD64[Frame->rax];
2864 
2865  long (*call)(SysFrm *, long, ...) = r_cst(long (*)(SysFrm *, long, ...),
2866  Syscall.Handler);
2867 
2868  if (unlikely(!call))
2869  {
